snippet.textDisplay: Today I lost my little dog, she was the love of my life, my best company, my best friend, unfortunately cancer took her too soon and I can't bear the pain of losing her. I think the worst thing is that I couldn't say goodbye to her, I wasn't at home and I couldn't give her one last cuddle and tell her how much I loved her, I feel so guilty about that, for not having done more for her. this is the worst day of my life so far, I lost the one I loved most in the world.
snippet.textOriginal: Today I lost my little dog, she was the love of my life, my best company, my best friend, unfortunately cancer took her too soon and I can't bear the pain of losing her. I think the worst thing is that I couldn't say goodbye to her, I wasn't at home and I couldn't give her one last cuddle and tell her how much I loved her, I feel so guilty about that, for not having done more for her. this is the worst day of my life so far, I lost the one I loved most in the world.

snippet.textDisplay: Often times my stress stems from not being in control. Weither it's not being in control of a situation, using time poorly, loosing control of myself or maybe even not being able to control others. However, this video reminds me that control is something that I was never ment to have except of myself. Even though I make mistakes in controlling myself, though, it's going to be ok because I am just a very small piece of a very big puzzle and even though I might not fit anywhere right now, that doesn't mean I don't have a place that I belong. I will find that place someday as all the pieces also find their place with me. So find your place too, where you don't have to control everything and where everything, even you and I, can just....be.

Idk if anyone will read it but i need to get this off my chest,
Life is really hard dude. I'm 18 (going 19 in October which is very close) and everything's so scary,
Since i was a child my dream was to go to university and experience that academic life...and i wasn't able to until now,
I've send my request and the exam will be soon which is scaring me to no end.
I'm afraid of messing it up and not being able to go to uni yet another year
And even thought i study almost 5 hours a day i still learn nothing and my head is too heavy i dont know what to do.
I don't wantnto disappoint my parents who are putting a lot of pressure on me also...
I can't imagine what i will do if i fail the exam

snippet.textOriginal:
Idk if anyone will read it but i need to get this off my chest,
Life is really hard dude. I'm 18 (going 19 in October which is very close) and everything's so scary,
Since i was a child my dream was to go to university and experience that academic life...and i wasn't able to until now,
I've send my request and the exam will be soon which is scaring me to no end.
I'm afraid of messing it up and not being able to go to uni yet another year
And even thought i study almost 5 hours a day i still learn nothing and my head is too heavy i dont know what to do.
I don't wantnto disappoint my parents who are putting a lot of pressure on me also...
I can't imagine what i will do if i fail the exam
What if I'm just nothing in the end, what about all those dreams...everything i planned for my life
What am i supposed to do if i am not the person i have thought to be all my life?
I don't have anyone to talk to about this..life is like the ocean and i am drawning, yet no one is there to help me out

snippet.textDisplay: This sound brings me back to a summer night in 2007, when my father was still alive. It was a hot summer night with no electricity. My whole family lay on a mat in the yard together, looking up at the sky with hundreds of bright stars.Almost 20 years later, I still remember every little moment. I suffered from depression for almost 10 years, my soul seemed dead. It was these memories of the past that kept me alive and trying. For a brief moment, I was no longer the sad 30 year old girl.I turned back into a 12 year old girl with sparkling eyes, lying in my father's warm arms.  I'm not sure about tomorrow but right now I feel so happy. I hope you do too.
snippet.textOriginal: This sound brings me back to a summer night in 2007, when my father was still alive. It was a hot summer night with no electricity. My whole family lay on a mat in the yard together, looking up at the sky with hundreds of bright stars.Almost 20 years later, I still remember every little moment. I suffered from depression for almost 10 years, my soul seemed dead. It was these memories of the past that kept me alive and trying. For a brief moment, I was no longer the sad 30 year old girl.I turned back into a 12 year old girl with sparkling eyes, lying in my father's warm arms.  I'm not sure about tomorrow but right now I feel so happy. I hope you do too.

snippet.textDisplay:
This comment will get lost among other people's, but if you're reading this, I want you to know that you can do it. Don't give up. If you had a bad day, it's in the past.
Think carefully about the future. You don't know when you'll leave the world or when someone you know will. You don't know what will happen if you do something. You don't know anything, so don't make up things that aren't true. Think positive. Because if not, you will attract bad things, such as envy, hatred, sadness, and sometimes disgust, etc.
Has someone you loved just died? It's okay. It can be a very difficult time, but the idea is to realize that not everything lasts forever, like a meal, school, animals, everything.
Are you having a bad day? Treat it as discipline. Life tests you to see if you're strong mentally, emotionally, physically, and much more. 
Did you break something precious? Don't worry, things come back, but in a different way and always different, nothing is the same as we know it.
Did a pet die? I know it may have been your best friend, but friends last FOREVER. They'll always be watching over you from somewhere above, somewhere unknown, but warm to them. They may have been in a painful state of mourning, just like us humans. They must leave; they want to stop the pain they feel. Therefore, they must leave, and not resist. It's part of nature.
Lastly, and most importantly, if you have any illness or disability, THINK POSITIVE. You will recover, you will be fine, nothing will go wrong, you are strong.

A huge virtual hug to everyone who is suffering from something. If you cut yourself, or something similar, STOP. It won't help anything; it'll only make everything worse. Even if it takes your mind off thinking and you enjoy the "peace" you feel in that situation, it only disconnects you from the world. And that is wrong, TOO WRONG, talk to someone who understands you, you can get a psychologist or therapist, but NEVER EVER IN YOUR LIFE do that.

Finally, again, goodbye to everyone, I hope this comment makes you reflect on things in life, a huge hug to everyone (as I said). And remember, stay on your feet, don't look back, walk, run as fast as you can to escape the past, let the chains break with YOUR strength. Not with someone else's (if that person doesn't help you).

Goodbye, take good care of yourselves. May your heart rest in peace and tranquility.ğŸ¤

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm just using this space to vent lol.

I sometimes get the feeling I don't belong. I feel lonely on a daily basis even though I'm surrounded by people everyday. I feel a constant urge of having it "figured out" and tbh... I don't... I don't know what I want to do with my life. I don't know who I am, what I like, who I like etc. Everything is moving so fast and I barely have time to take in precious moments or create fun memories. As big as my smile is.... as lonely is my heart... I don't know what it is I want or need but all I can say is.... I am tired... I just want to sleep because I feel like I don't belong. 

That's it from me. Be kind everyone. Even though I don't know y'all, I wish y'all happiness â¤

snippet.textDisplay:
In horrible stomach pain right now. I was sweating and I felt like I was about to vomit. A part of me was scared it was something serious. Then I got into a fetal position to ease the pain, and to distract myself I just started scrolling YouTube and I found this little video. Something about the music brings me back to warm summer days. The comments here are so heartfelt.

Slowly, I've started to feel the pain subside. It's still there but it's not hurting much. I'll be okay, I won't die. Outside my window, dawn approaches. 

Take care everyone.

Then I got into a fetal position to ease the pain, and to distract myself I just started scrolling YouTube and I found this little video. Something about the music brings me back to warm summer days. snippet.textDisplay:
Adulthood...

something I dreaded the most. I am 19 going 20 this year and I have just completed my internship of 5 months. It was not that smooth sailing but I've overcome it at the end. How I wish to be a kid/teenager forever studying in school and spending time with friends. They say: "you won't cherish the things you have until you lose them". This is quite true.

I am struggling with life, not making enough connections and relationships due to my introverted personality, not getting good enough grades to enter my dream uni course. All of it makes me fill that my life is unfulfilling and bland. 

Back to the point of adulthood, I cannot accept the fact that I'll have to work for the rest of my life until retirement. With little to no time of doing things I like. Honestly I am currently continuing my life due to the awesome people around me (families, some friends) , and hopefully a soulmate for me to complete my life with

This comment is a note to self to document down my life experiences and thoughts. I am positive that this would not be same thoughts after a few years time when I will go through Army and University, ultimately going in to the workforce and hopefully finding my love â¤.

snippet.textDisplay: I tried falling asleep to this, but I was so distracted by the fact that the bed is blocking the dresser. Like seriously, this room makes no sense. From the perspective, it appears as if the bed is both on the floor and tilted upward towards the window. It's genuinely impossible to tell if it's meant to have legs or not. And the fan looks like the kind your supposed to put on a desk or smth, but it's neck is still long enough to reach the top of the bed? And what's the point of the bookcase if all your crap is going to be on the floor? And where the frick is this man's room at, in the middle of fricking no where, no other buildings or people, where the moon and stars are at ground level? Wtf

I dont think anyone will read this but its 2am for me right now. 20 minutes till 3am and ive been crying this night. I was initially crying because i relapsed again but i was only 1 day clean. But then i started crying cause i felt ugly. Then it was because i felt scared for the future. Im really stessed and tired of everything. My room is really messy right now, but im too tired to clean up. I was talking to God about how im really scared of the future. I know my dreams, one of them is to dance. I wanna learn dance. I never really told anyone about it though because i never had the chance to, even if i did have that chance, i wouldnt say tell anyone. I think my dreams are stupid because i cant do them, and everyone will always be better than me. I told my parents i wanna be a doctor, i mean i told them that when i was a toddler. But now that im older, my dream's changed. I wanna dance but i realized how bad i am at it so i genuinely cant. Now that i cant do what i wanna do, im stuck. I dont know what i CAN do in the future now. So it makes me scared. What if i dont figure it out? What if i have to be a doctor but i know i dont wanna be that? But this video helped me. And it was heart warming to see people from around the world comment and comfort eachother. I think even in the darkest moments of our lives, theres still a tiny warm light thats worth to see.

Anyways, im hoping if anyone does see this little stupid comment of mine have a good day or night, rest and drink water ( Â´ â–½ ` ).ï½¡ï½â™¡ you all matter

snippet.textDisplay:
Greetings to all readers. I'm in Sweden and I've only been here a few days. I have now started my life here.
Basically I am from Pakistan. I don't understand my life. I feel like my life is like a dry leaf that has fallen from a tree and is blowing away with the wind. He has no will of his own, no choice... What I want is not happening and what I don't want is happening. At night, 00:31 o'clock I'm lying in my bed listening to this music and that's all I'm thinking about, about my life, about my future.

What I want is not happening and what I don't want is happening. snippet.textDisplay: somehow this song had made me relaxed a bit. been hurting myself for a long time and never felt that I could be free in my life. I always neglected how I felt because I deemed it useless and even if I were to express it, none would really care about it that much and I understand that. Everyone has their own problems after all. This is the first time I'm trying to express what I feel and i'm not really used to it.  It just feels wrong just talking about what I want or anything related to myself. I'm currently in a relationship but life's been more difficult ever since. There were times that I wished it remained that way so that I could live in peace. I'm fully aware of what's going on in my life and hurting myself has somewhat become my salvation to ease my emotions and be myself again. None knows about this aside from the person I'm in a relationship with. I kinda just want to let go of everything but here I am making a funny comment to unknown audience. If you read this far, thanks for your time, I appreciate it.

I don't know if this music is helping but I really need some good fucking luck this week. 
Because I feel like I'm going to snap at somebody if I don't.

Jesus Christ loves you!

1 John

2:15 Do not love the world or the things in it. If you love the world, you do not love God the Father.

I think some people are meant to be alone. I just want to be content with my life, thats all. I will be happy even doing a small job my whole life, thats all i want. a small job. ill be alright. And i wont complain about being lonely because i cant keep people close, not even my own. My parents would no longer be there one day and ill just have to with regret for my whole life. Im meant to live far away from everyone but thats ok ig. World is not exciting anymore than it was to me when i was young, i was hopeful and believed everyone is good. It all changed. I cant think the same anymore. I hope everything just feels okay one day when ill be on my bed or couch having coffee while relaxing. i would like to hear this music then but while feeling okay and not anxious like now. Im cold right now but im grateful for my blanket and bed right now, its keeping me warm in this cold early morning (632am) 
winters here. its goona hit my small town soon. It'll add more silence to my life than it already had. Guess winters work like that. its fine. 
i dont know what all i wrote but these are things that are in my head every second. 
anyways, idk why you read till here but take care, lets just try to be content with our lifes.

snippet.textDisplay: My girlfriend broke up with me and I found out she cheated on me.. I went through the stages of what a person go through finding out they got cheated on, I've cried for minutes, not silent, but a loud sob.. It was the time all what's suppressed in me was released, I couldn't hold it anymore.. And after that I couldn't cry anymore, there were no more tears.. My heart felt nothing, just empty.. Probably numb.. I still miss her to this day.. It pains me that I do.. And that I can't bring myself to be angry at her like I say I am.. But am I really though..? Sometimes I wish she would come back at me crying and regretting everything she did.. And I'd be an absolute fool for accepting her again with open arms.. But she won't.. She found someone better.. And all I could do is try to move on.. But, how? How do I do that when almost everything reminds me of her.. Have I done something so horrible to get this torture.. How do I heal and move on..? This was my first.. But if thus were to happen again It can be my last.. And I'd rather get hit.. to forget all of this dreadful nightmare and maybe just be in deep slumber forever.

snippet.textDisplay: For those who feel like they're too old to do something new, you aren't. For those too scared to go off the beaten path, do it if it makes you happy.  Most of all, the one thing I've truly learned in my 32 years on earth is that you really have no clue what your future is going to be like.  You don't know when you'll lose a loved one, you don't know who you might meet, you don't even know when your last day is! so just live.  My life looks nothing like I thought it would, but I am happy knowing that the unknown is actually a beautiful thing.  Trust in your creator. and TRUST YOUR HEART.

Birthdays, holidays, summer barbecues, gardening, watching game shows late at night, and especially Christmas. We love Christmas. I don't want to think about last Christmas being our last ğŸ˜” I can only pray that we'll be blessed with more time together.

snippet.textDisplay:
Lovely music. I am tired and sad in a way i havent really felt before. The end of last year had me cutting off so many people that were horrible to me. I went into conservation mode to cope with the pain until i could move on and find someone new and safer to trust myself with.
There has been someone ive wanted to befriend for a very long time. Last month, i finally built up the courage to be myself with them and friendship blossomed. For three weeks it was pure bliss. I left conservation mode, and finally, felt myself start opening up again. Fast forward to now, this person and i ended up in a conversation where we made fun of something personal to many people and their identities, and i realized i wasnt ok with that- just out of respect for others and out of the thought that i have considered identifying with the thing we made fun of. We have talked about it and this person has apologized. But i feel we didnt talk about it to the extent necessary and i do not know if their actions align with their words and intent. I don't know how to talk about it with them again. Im afraid to trust this person. Im afraid to be honest. In only a week my happiness turned to an open wound reminding me of the past people who destroyed my livelihood. I wonder if this new friend is not compatible with my values and the thought crushes me. Even more so when i look back and this new friend has consistently expressed care for me and wants to help me feel safe with them. Im tired. Im sad. Im hurt. I just want to feel safe and genuinely cared about again. I wish this would stop. I wish i could trust again. Most of all i dont want to feel alone again.

snippet.textDisplay: It's been a long day indeed.......searching for jobs, applying, going to interviews, waiting and waiting and wondering how and when everything will work out........plop on the couch in pajamas with a snack......wondering about a man I'm in love with and wondering if he loves me too the same way.....trying not to cry while listening to the sudden heavy rain fall outside.  Missing my kitty, thinking about him and how I wish he could've lived longer.  Thinking about heaven....and how earth time feels so long until I see him again.  Cleaning the house to distract myself and refrain from tears....plop down by my library to find a book, only make it a couple pages....phew......day felt longer in my head I think.....

snippet.textDisplay: I have been feeling tired and anxious for eight months. Months ago I was really anxious about my university music exam and I was very sad because the person I like lied to me and betrayed me. Today I feel many of these feelings because I couldn't live them at that moment, everything was too much for me, I was exhausted. I am proud of myself because I achieved my university exam, however, I am very afraid, will I be good enough? Will my colleagues accept me? Will I be able to achieve it? I'm tired and exhausted. And I continue to heal my broken heart. I feel like everything is too much, I have a lot of anxiety and music is the only thing that keeps me alive, thank youâ¤
